cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with face recognition using convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of discriminative nonlinear features and multi-stream multi-layer convolution networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the multiPIE dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the development of a new method for face recognition suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
